« Previous Page




      For Employees    


This page provides internal tools and support for employees of Leidos, including access to Prism, Deltek T&E, Outlook Web Access, IT Service Desk support, ethics training, and more. A Leidos username/password is required to access these resources.







Prism: Social Collaboration
Prism is the social business solution for internal communication and collaboration among Leidos employees.


Outlook Web Access
Connect to Microsoft Exchange remotely to access your Leidos email messages from your web browser.


Deltek T&E
Record your time and submit expenses using Deltek T&E, our web-based time-recording and expense system.

 
Additional Employee Resources

Leidos Benefits and Forms
			Leidos employees and their family members may download commonly used Leidos benefit claim forms and view information about updating benefits elections.


Leidos Stockholder Services
			The Stockholder Services section contains news and contact information to assist you with your shareholder and retirement needs, as well as answers to frequently asked questions regarding your stock ownership.


Employee Service Desk
			The Leidos IT Service Desk is a centralized support center for computing resources and information needs. If you are a Leidos employee and need help with a Leidos application, please contact the Service Desk.


Web Conferencing
			This tool allows employees and customers to share PowerPoint, Excel, and Word presentations with multiple users via a web browser.


Access Payroll Self Service Portal
			Get convenient online confidential access to your pay data, direct deposit, tax withholding, deductions and annual statements through the Payroll Self Service Portal. Though this resource is not managed by Leidos, help is available on Prism.


Download Remote Access Software
			View instructions for download and use of the VPN & Remote Access Software.


Travel Services
			Leidos Travel Services is staffed by dedicated Leidos employees who are experienced professionals ready to serve.


Ethics Training
			This site provides information on the Ethics Awareness Program and the various ways a Leidos employee can take the ethics training.


Password Management
			This tools allows Leidos employees to unlock or change their password without calling the help desk.











Need Help?
The Leidos Service Desk is a centralized support center for computing resources and information needs.
Contact the Service Desk »






 

 












 
 




