          About        




















We turn challenges into opportunities.

We bring a mix of innovative technology and sector expertise to customers in defense, intelligence, civil, and health markets. We look for solutions that not only transform businesses, but change the world.
View Our Capabilities


View Our Fact Sheet



                        Our approach to every challenge is HOLISTIC & SYSTEMATIC




                        We see solutions others can't with IMPACTFUL ANALYTICS




                        We make real life better with a HUMAN POINT-OF-VIEW










Our People.Our Communities.Our Environment.
We do business with respect and responsibility for all three.

At Leidos, we take responsibility for improving the quality of life of our employees, their families and the communities in which we live and work. Our commitment extends beyond the contributions we make to solve difficult problems through science and technology. More on Corporate Responsibility »








Our History

More than 40 years ago a small team of visionary scientists set out to solve big problems...
Learn More 





1970
Posted first profits; won a new relationship

Leidos posted a profit after its first year, much to its founder’s surprise, and established its first long-term client, the Defense Nuclear Agency.





1984
Helped design America’s Cup winner

We supported the technical design of the winning yacht for the America’s Cup and began conceptual design for a geologic nuclear waste repository in Nevada.





1996
Made a bold, strategic acquisition

The company’s entrepreneurial spirit and small-company flexibility kept us at the forefront of new technology. We acquired domain name registrar Network Solutions and became one of the largest providers of Internet and e-commerce services.





2008
Built first-of-its-kind solar community

We played a major role in helping Okotoks, Alberta become the first solar community in North America. Our Canadian subsidiary developed a solar-thermal system to capture energy from the summer sun and store it to heat homes through the long, cold winter.





2013
Formally split into Leidos and SAIC

The company officially split into Leidos, a $6 billion solutions-focused business, and SAIC, a $4 billion services business.





2016
COMBINES WITH LOCKHEED MARTIN'S IS&GS

Leidos expands to 32,000 employees across locations in 30 countries. The company reported pro forma annual revenues of approximately $10 billion for the fiscal year ended Jan. 1, 2016.








A Commitment to Quality
We take pride in the quality of our solutions and services. That’s why our standards are high and our commitment to quality is unwavering.

To us, quality means two things: satisfying our customers by delivering what they need on time and in budget and continuously improving processes so that our work is done right. Learn More »





