Corporate Leadership
View All »
Meet the executive team responsible for leading 32,000 forward thinking employees towards shared success.





Roger A. Krone
Chairman & CEO
Roger A. Krone is Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Leidos. With more than $10 billion in annual revenue and 32,000 employees worldwide, Leidos is a recognized global leader in solving important problems in the defense, intelligence, homeland security, civil, and health markets. Before being named CEO in July 2014,...
Learn More »






Leidos Subsidiaries
View All »




Leidos Biomedical Research, Inc.
Leidos Biomedical Research, Inc. develops and applies advanced technologies to help translate research discoveries into treatments for cancer and AIDS. It is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Leidos and dedicated to a single contract to the Frederick National Laboratory for Cancer Research.
Learn More »


Varec, Inc.
Varec, a wholly owned subsidiary of Leidos, has been a leading innovator in the petroleum and chemical sectors for 80+ years.
Learn More »


Systems Made Simple
From professional services and business strategy through user-centered requirements, design, development, implementation, and sustainment, Systems Made Simple, A Leidos Company, delivers the services needed to transform systems to improve outcomes, increase efficiencies, and reduce costs.
Learn More »


















 
 




